# MDX Components and Content Guidelines

## Component Structure

- All MDX components should be in `mdx-components/` directory
- Organize by category: `base/`, `code/`, `interactive/`, `layout/`
- Export components from category `index.ts` files
- Register all components in [mdx-components/index.tsx](mdc:mdx-components/index.tsx)

## Component Patterns

- Use `"use client"` directive for interactive components
- Wrap complex components with `MDXErrorBoundary` for error handling
- Use `IsInCodeBlockContext.Provider` for code-related components
- Implement proper TypeScript interfaces for all props

## MDX Content Guidelines

- Use proper frontmatter with required fields: `title`, `description`
- Follow consistent heading hierarchy (H1 for page title, H2 for sections)
- Use code blocks with language specification: ````typescript`
- Prefer semantic HTML elements over generic divs
- Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling

## Code Block Patterns

- Use `CodeGroup` for multiple code examples with tabs
- Use `CodePreviewBlock` for live preview + code combinations
- Always specify language for syntax highlighting
- Use `title` attribute for code block titles

## Content Organization

- Keep content files in `content/pages/` directory
- Use kebab-case for filenames
- Group related content in subdirectories
- Update navigation in [muni.config.ts](mdc:muni.config.ts) when adding pages
